{
  "texts": [
    "Such proof steps are ubiquitous in geometry proofs, yet not covered by geometric rules.",
    "We expand the Gaussian elimination process implemented in GeoLogic 19 to find the deduction closure for all possible linear operators in just seconds.",
    "Our symbolic deduction engine is an intricate integration of DD and AR, which we apply alternately to expand the joint closure of known true statements until expansion halts.",
    "This process typically finishes within a few seconds to at most a few minutes on standard non-accelerator hardware.",
    "There has not been a complete treatment for algebraic deduction in the literature of geometry theorem proving."
  ]
}